  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of security-related trainings to humanitarian personnel working on the Syria crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to support the provision of Safe Secured Approach Field Environment (SSAFE) training to provide essential security and safety awareness to all UN and associated personnel operating in southern Turkey bordering Syria where risk levels are high. This will be a continuation project for the provision of SSAFE trainings provided by IOM since 2017 and financially supported by SCHF since May 2019. The funding from the SCHF remains crucial to support the safety and security of humanitarian workers to conduct and deliver life-saving emergency assistance in a safe manner, as  there is a funding gap and no other source for this critical interagency service currently .

The total number of targeted beneficiaries for the project is 600 humanitarian staff working on the Syria response (360 men, 240 women). The trainings aim to assist in improving the security environment and preparedness of humanitarian staff within the current context.  

The trainings will be conducted in Gaziantep, Turkey, a hub for the Syria Cross-Border Response.</narrative>
  </description>
